Assad Vows to Overcome Crisis, Won’t Bend to Pressure, SANA Says

-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 
2011-12-09T06:26:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/assad-vows-to-overcome-crisis-won-t-bend-to-pressure-sana-says.html
Syria ’s President Bashar al-Assad
said his regime remains strong and will overcome the current
crisis without changing its positions “whatever the
pressures,” Syrian Arab  News Agency  reported.  “Syria is able to overcome the current events,” the
state-run news agency cited Assad as saying. “It won’t ever
give up its stances, principles and sovereignty,” Assad added,
according to the agency.  The Syrian president, who has come under increasing
international sanctions after a violent crackdown of protests
since March against the regime, also rejected “foreign
interference” in Syrian affairs, SANA reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nayla Razzouk in Dubai at 
